## Summary

- Adds `hostManaged` boolean option to `CliBackendConfig` (default: `true`, backward compatible)
- When `hostManaged: false`, the runner removes `CLAUDE_CODE_PROVIDER_MANAGED_BY_HOST` from the spawned CLI process environment
- Allows Claude CLI to use standard subscription billing instead of "extra usage" tier when orchestrated by OpenClaw

## Problem

When OpenClaw spawns Claude CLI via the `claude-cli` backend, it sets `CLAUDE_CODE_PROVIDER_MANAGED_BY_HOST=1` in the child process environment. This causes Anthropic to classify the usage as "extra usage" rather than subscription-included, even for users with Max/Pro subscriptions. Users get `402 "You're out of extra usage"` errors despite having available subscription capacity.

Direct `claude -p` calls from a terminal work fine (subscription-covered), but the same call spawned by OpenClaw's gateway gets billed differently due to the managed-by-host marker.

## Solution

Add a `hostManaged` option to `CliBackendConfig` that users can set to `false` via `agents.defaults.cliBackends` config:

```json
{
  "agents": {
    "defaults": {
      "cliBackends": {
        "claude-cli": {
          "command": "claude",
          "hostManaged": false
        }
      }
    }
  }
}
```

When `false`, the runner deletes `CLAUDE_CODE_PROVIDER_MANAGED_BY_HOST` from the spawned process env after the standard env construction, so the CLI behaves like a regular subscription session.

## Files changed

- `src/config/types.agent-defaults.ts` — Added `hostManaged?: boolean` to `CliBackendConfig`
- `src/config/zod-schema.core.ts` — Added zod validation for `hostManaged`
- `src/agents/cli-runner/execute.ts` — Delete managed-by-host env var when `hostManaged === false`
- `src/agents/cli-backends.test.ts` — Two new tests for opt-in/opt-out behavior

